  "local_port": 60970,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I retrieve deleted messages on messenger?",
  "response": "If you've accidentally deleted messages on Facebook Messenger, retrieving them can be challenging, as deleted messages are usually permanently removed from your account. However, there are a few steps you can take to try and recover or find those messages:\n\n1. **Check Archived Threads**: Sometimes, you may have archived a conversation instead of deleting it.\n   - Open Facebook Messenger.\n   - Click on your profile picture and select \"Archived Threads.\"\n   - Look for the conversation there.\n\n2. **Download Your Facebook Data**: Sometimes, old messages might be included in the data that Facebook lets you download.\n   - Go to Facebook and click on the down arrow in the top-right corner.\n   - Select \"Settings & Privacy,\" then \"Settings.\"\n   - In the left-hand column, click on \"Your Facebook Information.\"\n   - Click on \"Download Your Information.\"\n   - Select the data you want to download (make sure to select \"Messages\").\n   - Click \"Create File.\" Once the file is ready, download it and check for your messages.\n\n3. **Contact the Other Person**: If you deleted the messages but the other person didn't, they might still have the conversation intact and can forward the messages back to you.\n\n4. **Check Email Notifications**: If you have email notifications enabled for Messenger, some of your old messages might be found in your email inbox.\n   - Search your email for keywords related to the conversation.\n\n5. **Use Third-Party Apps**: Be cautious with this step, as third-party apps claiming to recover deleted messages could be unreliable or pose security risks. It's important to only use reputable software and be mindful of your privacy and security.\n\nSimply put, once a message is deleted from Facebook Messenger, there isn't an official method to recover it from Facebook servers. Backing up your data periodically could help in preventing loss of important messages in the future.",
